==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decker
<hw>Deck"er</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, decks or adorns; a coverer; <as>as, a table
<ex>decker</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vessel or vehicle which has a deck or decks; --
used esp. in composition; <as>as, a single-<ex>decker</ex>; a
three-<ex>decker</ex>; a double-<ex>decker</ex> bus.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deckle</ent>⟦br⟧
